# Shell Script Execution Rule

- On Windows, execute `.sh` files with Git Bash instead of PowerShell or CMD.
- Preferred command format: `& "C:\Program Files\Git\bin\bash.exe" <script_path> [args]`.
- If `bash` is unavailable in `PATH`, do not call `bash <script>` directly.

```bash
# BAD on Windows when bash is not in PATH
bash publish/publish.sh ui_builder

# GOOD
& "C:\Program Files\Git\bin\bash.exe" publish/publish.sh ui_builder
```
